<pre><code>char *str = "string" ; char *end = str; while(*(end+1) != '\0') {     end++; }  while(str &lt; end) {     char temp = *str;     *str = *end;     *end = temp;     str++;     end--; }` </code></pre>  <p>EDIT:  Are both these<code>*str = *end</code>,  <code>*str++ = *end</code> invalid?</p>  <p>The above code gives error at that line.</p>  <p>Aren't <code>str</code> and <code>end</code> pointing to a read only part in memory whether it be post increment?</p>